description: From porter (“person who carries luggage and related objects”) +‎ -age (suffix forming nouns indicating an action, process, or result; a charge, fee, or toll; or a relationship or state).

entries.meaning: (uncountable) The carrying or transportation of goods by a porter (“person who carries luggage and related objects”) or other person.
(uncountable, obsolete, rare) Goods or other things which are carried; burdens.
(countable, uncountable) The charge for such carrying or transportation.

description: From porter (“person in control of the entrance to a building”) +‎ -age (suffix forming nouns indicating a relationship or state).

entries.meaning: The occupation of, or services provided by, a porter (“person in control of the entrance to a building”).
